Introduction¶This is my first notebook blogpost. This post is dedicated to trying and finding all capabilities of blogging with nikola and jupyter notebook. This will contain some math rendering, code, plots, graphs etc...


Findings so far :-

1. We need to add jquery, momentjs and requirejs on top of the notebook/ header(perhaps via cdn) to be able to display holoviews, bokeh and plotly
2. Interactive widgets from ipywidgets doesn't work as expected. I will try to stick around with paramnb and try it out in future
3. Unable to render mpld3 plots from notebook yet.
4. mpld3 causes certain issues. Need further investigation






In [1]:


import os
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

import scipy as sp
import sklearn 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import holoviews as hv
import hvplot
import plotly.plotly

import plotly.graph_objs as go
from ipywidgets import interactive # This will not work in rendered notebook









